Did you know that an alarming 22% of Canadian millennials have not heard, or are unsure if they have heard, of the Holocaust; and 62% of Canadian millennials were not aware that 6 million Jews were killed in the Holocaust? (according to the Holocaust Knowledge and Awareness Survey by the Claims Conference) WE CAN CHANGE THIS. 

January 27 is International Holocaust Remembrance Day, a day to remember the six million Jewish children, women, and men murdered by the Nazis during the Holocaust, the #Shoah.

Let’s honour their memory. Support the World Jewish Congress’ #WeRemember social media campaign by downloading the #WeRemember sign at the link in bio and posting on your socials a photo of you holding it.  

Together, let us renew our collective vow: #NeverAgain.

Tag @cijainfo and @WorldJewishCongress so that, in partnership with the Auschwitz Memorial and Museum your post is displayed at the site of the former Auschwitz-Birkenau death camp on January 26 and 27. #WeRemember

Honoured to be featured in the lucky 8th edition of @fetechinoise Magazine and thrilled to have been asked to emcee at tonight’s Fete Chinoise Lunar New Year Gala, celebrating Chinese culture in a Canadian context. Today is International Women’s Day. Tomorrow is her birthday. The Tiger Boss of my life and the baddest bitch I know – my ma, the Chinese Squawking Chicken, aka Judy Yeung Kwai Fong, born 9 March 1950, posing for her first magazine shoot for Fête Chinoise Edition 8: Into the Unknown 未知 · 未來.

Hilariously, before we got there, she was pretending like she didn’t want to be photographed, that it wasn’t in her nature to be in the spotlight. Please. Within five minutes she’d raided the clothing rack. Half an hour later she was obsessed with her makeup. Ten minutes after that she was serving looks for the camera.

Thanks to the team @fetechinoise for this wonderful opportunity to feature the woman who has been the guiding force of my life. “Boiled down to basics, mom is the sergeant major, daughter the foot soldier enlisted to carry out her commands.” I will follow for as long as she’s around to command me. Ma is living with an incurable disease – and every day that she wakes up to fight is a gift. As I say in the article (link in bio), I plan to make her immortal. I watch a lot of reenactments of Chinese mythology, and I can tell you that we are obsessed with immortality, and so this— talking about my mother like this — is how to achieve immortality for her. She’s a larger-than-life person. To me, it’s only fitting that she lives on forever. #fetechinoise #internationalwomensday

Asian artists made history this year with a record number of Oscar nominations. My Oscar look on @etalkCTV is meant to honour this achievement. I call it “Orchid Rules the World” and I’m so grateful to Jordan Stewart @rvng.couture for realising my vision. The idea for the dress came from a character called Bai Feng Xi in the Wuxia drama series “Who Rules the World”. Bai Fengxi is one of the most skilled martial artists of her time, and also a warrior queen. In episode 36, during a battle strategy meeting with her generals, she wears a white military robe with gold leaf armoured shoulders – this became the origin of my dress (swipe to see). The collar and the long cuffs are classic kung fu style inspired by the costumes in the now legendary 1983 series “Legend of the Condor Heroes” that I watched when I was a kid in Hong Kong (swipe to see). The inspiration for my hair is from the hit 2022 Xianxia drama “Love Between Fairy and Devil” and the female lead, Orchid, who becomes the Goddess of Healing (swipe to see). These stories, which are rooted in Taoism and Buddhism and involve mythology and fantasy, explore renewal, spiritual energy and awakening, and are well-known in Chinese popular culture. Many of these same themes are explored in the Oscar-nominated film Everything Everywhere All At Once. And of course Michelle Yeoh is no stranger to Wuxia. Crouching Tiger Hidden Dragon!
 
My love and appreciation to our @etalkCTV stylist, @simonefaloona for guiding us through this process, patiently listening to all my TED Talks about Chinese entertainment fashion, even more patiently watching scenes from Chinese shows, and bringing all these traditional elements to life in a contemporary and thoroughly modern way. My endless gratitude to all the incredibly talented artists who helped put this look together. Happy Oscars 2023!

It’s been 43 years since Terry Fox began his Marathon of Hope and ever since, Canadians have been sharing what Terry Fox has meant to them. The Terry Fox Foundation is kicking off the annual Terry Fox Run with this limited edition t-shirt designed in collaboration with Ryan Reynolds @vancityreynolds that features messages of appreciation, drawings, and words of gratitude from people around the world who’ve been inspired by Terry’s story and legacy. 

My ma and our family have benefited from the critical cancer research that the Terry Fox Foundation has supported as she’s had two rounds of chemotherapy and two stem cell transplants, along with radiation, to treat multiple myeloma related to POEMS syndrome. Cancer research has extended her life and her time with us. 

Purchase a t-shirt at terryfox.org and register to join the annual Terry Fox Run on Sunday, September 17, 2023. All proceeds support critical cancer research.

Read your own message to Terry and share a photo of yourself in the t-shirt with #DearTerry and tag @TerryFoxFoundation to continue the spirit of his run! Thanks for your support!

#AD Turning 50 in September! As vain as I am, I’m not afraid of it. I feel great, I’m as active and engaged as I’ve ever been. Also, I like my face! And I don’t see aging as fighting my face but rather enhancing it. So this is me, trying out a @thermagecanada treatment at @rejuuvmedi for the first time that will help enhance my face, my eyes in particular. Lately I’ve noticed that my eyeliner is transferring because of increased hooding from my eyelids, which makes me look more tired than I am. I have so much energy, I want my eyes to reflect it.
 
Thermage® is a Health Canada approved skin tightening device that is indicated to treat the eyelids.

It’s a radiofrequency treatment, non-invasive, that can help to smooth, tighten, and contour skin. The downtime is minimal, I can basically go from treatment lights to studio lights and HD cameras right away.
 
Check my stories and feed because I’ll be documenting my Thermage® experience and, of course, the results, over the next couple of months. 
 
For more information follow the link in my bio with details about the treatment and also their promotion if you want to try for yourself.

#sponsored Half an hour after I started reading Tomorrow, and Tomorrow, and Tomorrow by @gabriellezevin I wanted to stop – not because I didn’t love it, but because I loved it so much I wanted to read it WITH my friends, especially my work friends, my co-collaborators.
 
This is a story about friendship, about creative romance, about the collective experience of falling in love with what you build together. There’s the bliss of discovery, that spark you get when you meet someone who both challenges and inspires you; you spend those early days chasing that feeling, that rush of affection and admiration; then you settle into the safety and security of your relationship; and of course inevitably, here come the bumps. Like all sweeping romances, creative romances will encounter those too.
 
And Tomorrow, and Tomorrow, and Tomorrow IS a sweeping romance that reads like an oral history of your favourite romantic film, or show, or album. Sadie and Sam’s relationship is exhilarating and devastating and healing and provocative, reminding us why, for the sake of what we love, we will try, and try, and try again.
 
A global bestseller, everyone from the New York Times to Indigo and the Globe & Mail named Tomorrow, and Tomorrow, and Tomorrow as one of the best books of 2022. One year later and it’s living up to its name. This is the book people are still talking about, it was the hottest book of the summer of 2023, it’s the book that is so good it keeps finding new readers; there will be more tomorrow, and tomorrow, and tomorrow. Which is why it’s the Indigo Fiction Staff Pick of the Month for September. Can’t wait to hear what you think of it. Let me know below. 
 
@penguincanada 
#tomorrowandtomorrowandtomorrow

Jeanne Beker is a television LEGEND – I’ve spent hundreds if not thousands of hours watching her on Fashion Television, reporting from every runway in the world. But I never, ever, ever would have imagined that I’d have the honour of sitting next to her at a fashion show! Here we are at the 20th annual Cashmere Collection featuring the work of 20 incredible Canadian designers who’ve all made garments with @CashmereCanada bathroom tissue! It is incredible what these artists have been able to create. And it’s even more incredible what the Cashmere Collection has achieved over these years, donating over $5 million to the breast cancer cause, becoming one of the top five partners at the Canadian Cancer Society, and among the leading contributors to the Quebec Breast Cancer Foundation.
 
The theme of the 2023 Cashmere Collection is LOVESTRUCK – and to mark the anniversary, @thejeannebekerand I are part of a documentary by the same name, Cashmere Presents: LOVESTRUCK, exploring the intimate relationship between emotion and fashion. Clothes aren’t just what we put on; they hold our memories, they convey our moods, they express our love. And love, sometimes, is messy. The documentary covers all of love’s delights and messes through fashion analysis and an exhilarating trip through the fashion archives. You’ll also be able to see the Cashmere Collection designs from this year’s runway. I am so proud to be part of this campaign and so honoured to have been included in this show …which premieres TODAY on @CraveCanada and CTVA.ca. Use the link in bio to dedicate your favourite to someone you love and $1 will be donated to the breast cancer cause, up to $50,000.
 
Photo credit: @georgepimentel1

I am LOVESTRUCK! That’s the theme of the 2023 Cashmere Collection featuring the work of 20 Canadian designers all using Cashmere bathroom tissue. Every single look is extraordinary, and the one that I wanted to wear most was by @daviddixoninc (see second slide) – which is why I’ve dedicated it to my ma, who has battled cancer (twice!) in her own LOVESTRUCK way: with self-love, a deep love and belief in herself. With every dedication, @CashmereCanada will donate $1 to the breast cancer cause, up to $50,000,. and with every purchase of a specially marked package of Cashmere bathroom tissue, they will donate $1 dollar to the breast cancer cause, up to $100,000. To dedicate your favourite garment, check the link in my bio and browse through the LOVESTRUCK Cashmere Collection. These looks are SO beautiful!
